1
00:00:06,465 --> 00:00:25,776
♪

2
00:00:25,776 --> 00:00:28,237
(hooves stomping)

3
00:00:29,655 --> 00:00:31,823
Rider, over there.

4
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:42,084
♪

5
00:00:42,084 --> 00:00:43,794
Are you scared, boy?

6
00:00:44,836 --> 00:00:47,089
Yeah, I'm scared.

7
00:00:47,089 --> 00:00:50,342
I'm wondering if
this is what you mean

8
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:53,971
when you say that
your heart is dancing.

9
00:00:53,971 --> 00:00:58,141
Hm, it seems you're finally
starting to understand.

10
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:03,230
♪

11
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:04,982
(engine rumbling)

12
00:01:06,525 --> 00:01:08,235
The enemy is inside.

13
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:23,292
♪

14
00:01:23,292 --> 00:01:27,004
(explosions)

15
00:01:29,965 --> 00:01:32,593
Berserker?

16
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:35,095
(singing in Japanese)

17
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:52,946
♪

18
00:03:10,399 --> 00:03:12,984
Are they having a party here?

19
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:15,654
Where is that little
chariot of yours?

20
00:03:15,654 --> 00:03:18,990
Well, the thing is,

21
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:23,495
I'm embarrassed to say I
lost it to Saber in a battle.

22
00:03:23,495 --> 00:03:25,831
Did you forget my decision?

23
00:03:25,831 --> 00:03:27,833
I believe I told you
that I would fight

24
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,335
and defeat you when you
were at full strength.

25
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,505
True, the weapons at my
disposal are somewhat depleted.

26
00:03:33,505 --> 00:03:37,509
However, Iskandar tonight
is less than perfect,

27
00:03:37,509 --> 00:03:40,762
and thus, is far greater
than perfection itself.

28
00:03:41,972 --> 00:03:43,974
So I see.

29
00:03:43,974 --> 00:03:46,935
Indeed the aura that
is emanating from you

30
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:49,020
is unusually potent.

31
00:03:50,814 --> 00:03:53,733
It appears you have come
before me actually believing

32
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:56,862
that you have a
chance of victory.

33
00:03:56,862 --> 00:03:57,904
Hm.

34
00:04:06,705 --> 00:04:09,875
King of Babylonia, a final word.

35
00:04:09,875 --> 00:04:12,502
Our banquet's last question.

36
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:15,046
I shall allow it, speak.

37
00:04:15,046 --> 00:04:17,549
Well, this is purely
hypothetical of course,

38
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:21,386
but were my Ionioi Hetairoi
armed with your Gate of Babylon,

39
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:25,056
it would create the most
powerful army imaginable.

40
00:04:25,056 --> 00:04:26,683
Hm, so?

41
00:04:28,351 --> 00:04:31,062
Why would you not
ally yourself with me?

42
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:34,065
The two of us together
could conquer the universe

43
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:36,526
and beyond if we desired it.

44
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:39,446
(laughing)

45
00:04:39,446 --> 00:04:43,033
You never cease to
amuse me, mongrel.

46
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:46,077
It has been ages since I
laughed so hard at gibberish

47
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:49,873
spouted by one
who is not a fool.

48
00:04:49,873 --> 00:04:53,168
But unfortunately,
I have had one comrade

49
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:55,670
and he is all I ever
intend to have.

50
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:59,758
Furthermore, there is no need
for there to be two kings.

51
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:02,260
The lonely path
of kingship, eh?

52
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:04,554
With all respect
due to a king,

53
00:05:04,554 --> 00:05:08,058
I shall challenge your
strong unwavering spirit.

54
00:05:08,058 --> 00:05:11,061
Very well, show me what
you think you can do,

55
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:13,271
King of Conquerors.

56
00:05:13,271 --> 00:05:16,775
You are a usurper truly
worthy of my judgment.

57
00:05:24,282 --> 00:05:25,450
(clank)

58
00:05:30,497 --> 00:05:33,750
Are you guys actually
friends with each other?

59
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,461
I could hardly be
unfriendly to him.

60
00:05:36,461 --> 00:05:39,339
After all, he may very well be

61
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:41,758
the last person I ever see.

62
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:47,889
Don't be stupid, you're not
gonna be killed here today.

63
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:49,558
I won't allow it!

64
00:05:49,558 --> 00:05:51,101
Have you forgotten
my command seal?

65
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:56,314
You are right, ha.

66
00:05:56,314 --> 00:05:58,191
You are exactly right.

67
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:04,990
Gather here, my
glorious comrades!

68
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:07,993
Tonight we shall become
the greatest legends

69
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:10,287
in all of eternity!

70
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:25,176
♪

71
00:06:25,176 --> 00:06:28,096
Our enemy is the
mighty King of Heroes,

72
00:06:28,096 --> 00:06:30,557
a most worthy opponent.

73
00:06:30,557 --> 00:06:34,561
My warriors, let us show
the first heroic spirit

74
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,689
our noble path of
ultimate conquest!

75
00:06:37,689 --> 00:06:40,358
(cheering)

76
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:43,028
♪

77
00:06:43,028 --> 00:06:46,281
(shouting)

78
00:06:46,281 --> 00:06:52,370
♪

79
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:55,498
Come to me, Lord of
Conquering armies.

80
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:59,836
Now you will be privileged to
behold the sight of a true king.

81
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:03,632
(yelling)

82
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:10,972
(explosions)

83
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:35,372
♪

84
00:07:35,372 --> 00:07:38,541
(breathing unevenly)

85
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:41,795
(groaning)

86
00:07:41,795 --> 00:07:53,556
♪

87
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,558
Why are you suffering so much?

88
00:07:57,686 --> 00:07:59,854
Because of Berserker.

89
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:02,357
He must fight a
battle right now,

90
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:04,401
and needs mana.

91
00:08:04,401 --> 00:08:06,986
Why?

92
00:08:06,986 --> 00:08:09,823
Because that priest said so.

93
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:13,952
‐That priest?
‐Yeah.

94
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:16,955
He made a promise to
me that he'd give me

95
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:20,500
the Grail once he got it.

96
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:24,295
If I have the Grail,
I can save you, Sakura.

97
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:26,965
You're going to save me?

98
00:08:28,383 --> 00:08:29,968
Yeah, of course.

99
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:34,264
Remember, I promised that
we would all play together

100
00:08:34,264 --> 00:08:37,976
like we used to with
your mom and sister.

101
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:42,897
Then I'll be able
to see Mother again?

102
00:08:42,897 --> 00:08:44,941
See your mother.

103
00:08:44,941 --> 00:08:47,902
♪

104
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:54,325
(screaming)

105
00:08:54,325 --> 00:08:58,038
(gunfire)

106
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:13,678
♪

107
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,847
Ahhh!

108
00:09:15,847 --> 00:09:23,354
♪

109
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:24,689
(shouting)

110
00:09:26,775 --> 00:09:28,568
Now.

111
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:31,821
♪

112
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:33,490
No good.

113
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:46,461
♪

114
00:09:46,461 --> 00:09:48,713
Can he see it?

115
00:09:48,713 --> 00:10:00,725
♪

116
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:03,520
He knows the lengths
of my blade.

117
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:06,731
Could he be some
knight I once knew?

118
00:10:08,817 --> 00:10:12,237
From your skill I assume you
to be a knight of some renown,

119
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:16,658
and so I ask, if you know
me to be Arturia Pendragon,

120
00:10:16,658 --> 00:10:20,245
King of Britain and
founder of Camelot...

121
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:24,165
...name yourself right now
as a knight's pride demands.

122
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:26,334
Challenging me with
your identity concealed

123
00:10:26,334 --> 00:10:29,337
is tantamount
to using deceit.

124
00:10:29,337 --> 00:10:33,091
(growling)

125
00:10:33,091 --> 00:10:35,468
(evil laughter)

126
00:10:36,469 --> 00:10:38,054
Who are you?

127
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:48,523
♪

128
00:10:48,523 --> 00:10:50,608
Impossible.

129
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:54,654
♪

130
00:10:54,654 --> 00:10:56,156
That's Arondight.

131
00:10:57,615 --> 00:10:59,617
It can't be you.

132
00:10:59,617 --> 00:11:02,620
(growling)

133
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:06,958
♪

134
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:08,543
(loud clang)

135
00:11:08,543 --> 00:11:16,593
♪

136
00:11:16,593 --> 00:11:19,721
Sir Lancelot.

137
00:11:19,721 --> 00:11:22,849
(growling)

138
00:11:30,523 --> 00:11:33,651
But why, my friend?

139
00:11:33,651 --> 00:11:35,904
You were esteemed as
the greatest of all

140
00:11:35,904 --> 00:11:37,780
the Knights of
the Round Table.

141
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:41,367
How can you be Berserker?

142
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:42,243
(grunting)

143
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:45,413
Stop!

144
00:11:46,915 --> 00:11:48,750
(shouting)

145
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:52,045
Lancelot.

146
00:11:52,045 --> 00:11:54,422
(groaning)

147
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:03,014
You may indeed
have saved them,

148
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:04,766
but you never led them.

149
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:08,519
Because I never
really led them.

150
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:11,314
Enraptured by a false
idol of a humble king

151
00:12:11,314 --> 00:12:13,233
who always serves others.

152
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:16,236
My ideals, my kingship.

153
00:12:16,236 --> 00:12:17,737
You're just a little girl.

154
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:20,073
Did how I rule
drive you to this?

155
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:23,243
(snarling)

156
00:12:29,415 --> 00:12:31,292
Please stop, Lancelot.

157
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:36,047
(army screaming)

158
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:45,390
Uniting dreams beneath
a banner of conquest.

159
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:47,350
I praise your
efforts at least.

160
00:12:49,310 --> 00:12:52,981
But foolish warriors,
have you not learned?

161
00:12:52,981 --> 00:12:56,025
♪

162
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:58,569
Dreams disappear when
the dreamer wakes,

163
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:01,864
every last one of them
with no exception.

164
00:13:01,864 --> 00:13:23,428
♪

165
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:26,597
Therefore, it was
inevitable that I would be

166
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:28,975
the one to stand in your way.

167
00:13:29,767 --> 00:13:32,061
King of Conquerors,

168
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:35,940
now know the end of
your eternal dream.

169
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:38,609
I shall show you
the stark reality.

170
00:13:40,403 --> 00:13:41,779
Here it comes!

171
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:45,324
Now, awaken Ea!

172
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:48,244
A stage worthy of
you has been set!

173
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:50,788
♪

174
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:54,417
Look up and behold,
at my liege!

175
00:13:54,417 --> 00:13:58,713
♪

176
00:13:58,713 --> 00:13:59,881
Hang on, boy!

177
00:13:59,881 --> 00:14:11,642
♪

178
00:14:11,642 --> 00:14:13,895
What?

179
00:14:13,895 --> 00:14:17,023
(rumbling)

180
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:22,945
That sword is the
Anti‐Universe Noble Phantasm

181
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:25,031
that can destroy all creation?

182
00:14:25,031 --> 00:14:28,493
♪

183
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:31,746
(crowd screaming)

184
00:14:31,746 --> 00:15:00,066
♪

185
00:15:07,281 --> 00:15:09,075
Hm.

186
00:15:11,536 --> 00:15:12,662
Rider.

187
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:21,212
I just remembered, there
is something important

188
00:15:21,212 --> 00:15:22,713
that I must ask you.

189
00:15:26,008 --> 00:15:28,052
Master Waver Velvet,

190
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:31,222
would you be willing
to serve as my retainer?

191
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:35,434
(breathing shakily)

192
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:39,689
♪

193
00:15:39,689 --> 00:15:40,815
You...

194
00:15:42,525 --> 00:15:45,027
...you are my king, sire.

195
00:15:45,027 --> 00:15:48,531
I will serve
you with devotion.

196
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:52,118
Do me the honor of leading me.

197
00:15:52,118 --> 00:15:54,453
Let me dream what you dream.

198
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:58,374
Ah, very well.

199
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:05,923
♪

200
00:16:05,923 --> 00:16:09,552
As king, my duty is to
inspire others to dream,

201
00:16:09,552 --> 00:16:13,681
and as my retainer, it is your
sacred duty to see my dream

202
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:17,310
to the end and share it
with future generations.

203
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:23,399
♪

204
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:25,443
Now live, Waver.

205
00:16:25,443 --> 00:16:27,111
See all of this through.

206
00:16:27,111 --> 00:16:29,780
Live long and tell
everyone you meet

207
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:32,533
of how your king
comported himself,

208
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:35,244
of the last charge of Iskandar.

209
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:37,997
♪

210
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:40,458
(cries)

211
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:46,756
All right, it is time
to go, Bucephalus!

212
00:16:46,756 --> 00:16:48,382
(horse neighing)

213
00:16:50,134 --> 00:16:51,552
Rider!

214
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:53,846
Glory lies beyond the horizon.

215
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:56,557
Challenge the unattainable.

216
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:59,310
Speak of conquest
and make it real

217
00:16:59,310 --> 00:17:02,897
for my men and for those
who watch behind me.

218
00:17:02,897 --> 00:17:05,107
♪

219
00:17:05,107 --> 00:17:08,110
(yelling)

220
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:25,795
♪

221
00:17:25,795 --> 00:17:28,923
(screaming)

222
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:52,863
♪

223
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:54,448
(clank)

224
00:17:55,783 --> 00:17:57,743
(chain jingling)

225
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,001
Hm.

226
00:18:07,753 --> 00:18:11,716
I swear to the gods, it
is just one strange toy

227
00:18:11,716 --> 00:18:14,385
after another with
you, isn't it?

228
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:15,511
(grunts)

229
00:18:19,056 --> 00:18:23,561
Have you awakened from your
dream, King of Conquerors?

230
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,319
I suppose I have.

231
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:34,864
However, once again,

232
00:18:34,864 --> 00:18:38,784
during this glorious campaign,

233
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:42,455
my heart was able to
dance a good deal.

234
00:18:46,083 --> 00:18:49,253
Feel free to challenge me
again as often as you like,

235
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:51,672
King of Conquerors.

236
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:58,804
This entire world is my garden
until the very end of time.

237
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:01,682
Thus, I guarantee you this,

238
00:19:01,682 --> 00:19:03,726
it will never bore you.

239
00:19:03,726 --> 00:19:06,604
It will always
be entertaining.

240
00:19:06,604 --> 00:19:08,064
(sighing)

241
00:19:09,732 --> 00:19:13,277
(waves crashing)

242
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:16,405
That sounds very good.

243
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:27,708
Now I see.

244
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,920
It was the beating of my heart

245
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:35,049
that was the sound
of Oceanus' waves.

246
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:45,851
(sniffling)

247
00:19:45,851 --> 00:20:07,748
♪

248
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:11,877
Child, are you Rider's master?

249
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:14,672
No, I'm not.

250
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:17,174
I am his retainer.

251
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:19,260
Hm?

252
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:20,636
I see.

253
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:26,851
But child, if you are truly
a loyal subject to him,

254
00:20:26,851 --> 00:20:30,229
your duty now is to avenge
your fallen sovereign.

255
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:32,148
♪

256
00:20:32,148 --> 00:20:34,984
If I challenge you, I'll die.

257
00:20:34,984 --> 00:20:36,652
Yes, of course you will.

258
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:40,239
I can't do that.

259
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:43,033
I was ordered by
him to survive.

260
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:54,462
♪

261
00:20:54,462 --> 00:20:56,630
Your loyalty is splendid.

262
00:20:56,630 --> 00:21:00,009
Never allow anything
to tarnish it.

263
00:21:00,009 --> 00:21:09,560
♪

264
00:21:09,560 --> 00:21:13,314
(crying)

265
00:21:13,314 --> 00:21:16,233
♪

266
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:18,736
He restoreth my soul.

267
00:21:18,736 --> 00:21:21,781
He leadeth me in paths
of righteousness

268
00:21:21,781 --> 00:21:24,450
for his name's sake.

269
00:21:24,450 --> 00:21:26,827
Yea, though I walk
through the valley

270
00:21:26,827 --> 00:21:28,746
of the shadow of death,

271
00:21:28,746 --> 00:21:31,165
I will fear no evil,

272
00:21:31,165 --> 00:21:34,502
for thou art with me.

273
00:21:34,502 --> 00:21:37,254
Thy rod and thy staff,

274
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:39,006
they comfort me.

275
00:21:39,006 --> 00:21:41,717
Thou preparest a
table before me.

276
00:21:41,717 --> 00:21:44,595
Thou anointest
my head with oil.

277
00:21:44,595 --> 00:21:46,806
